Temporal matching strategy. Options:
  \describe{
    \item{`"exact"`}{Exact date match (same-day temperature for acute heat-related mortality).}
    \item{`"discrete_lag"`}{Climate value exactly L days before event.}
    \item{`"moving_window"`}{Mean/sum of sliding window (t-W, t). **RECOMMENDED** for cumulative exposure.}
    \item{`"offset_window"`}{Aggregates historical interval (t-W2, t-W1),

Logical. If `TRUE` (default), implements two-level caching:
  \itemize{
    \item **Session cache**: In-memory cache (MD5 hash of parameters)
    \item **Disk cache**: Parquet files with Zstandard compression
  }
  Use `unlink(cache_dir, recursive = TRUE)` to clear all caches.

Logical. If `TRUE` (default), enables **two levels** of parallelism:
  \itemize{
    \item **Between years**: Multiple years downloaded simultaneously
    \item **Within year**: CSV files for each year parsed in parallel
  }
  For single-year imports, only within-year parallelization applies.

Character. Message language. One of:
  \itemize{
    \item `"pt"`: Portuguese (default)
    \item `"en"`: English
    \item `"es"`: Spanish
  }

Character. Message language. One of:
  \itemize{
    \item `"pt"`: Portuguese (default)
    \item `"en"`: English
    \item `"es"`: Spanish
  }

Character string specifying output format. Options:
  \itemize{
    \item `"browser"` - Interactive HTML in web browser (default)
    \item `"console"` - Simple list in R console
  }

Character. Temporal resolution of source files:
  \itemize{
    \item `"monthly"` (default) — one file per month (~5–20 MB each);
      returns mm/month.
    \item `"daily"` — one file per day (~3 MB each); returns mm/day.
      Recommended only for short periods; a full year = 365 downloads.
    \item `"annual"` — one file per year; returns mm/year.
  }
